com.google.crypto.tink

Class KeyManagerBase<P,KeyProto extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite,KeyFormatProto extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.crypto.tink.KeyManagerBase<P,KeyProto,KeyFormatProto>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KeyManager<P>

    @Alpha
public abstract class KeyManagerBase<P,KeyProto extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite,KeyFormatProto extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite>
extends Object
implements KeyManager<P>
    A utility class to implement a KeyManager.

    Implementing many of the methods in the KeyManager can be repetitive. This is an internal utility class to implement these methods. In order to instantiate it, one calls the constructor with class objects of the protos used and the type URL: 

     
 class MyConcreteKeyManager
     extends KeyManagerBase {
   public MyConcreteKeyManager() {
     super(ConcreteKeyProto.class, ConcreteKeyFormatProto.class, TYPE_URL);
   }
   [...]
 }
    Furthermore, one implements all the abstract methods in this class. This code is currently Alpha and may change without warning.
